34 With the feet I rested and with the eyes I passed 35 from there beyond the small stream, to gaze 36 the great variation of the fresh ones;
37 and there appeared to me, as it appears 38 suddenly a thing that diverts 39 by wonder all other thought,
40 a woman alone who was going 41 and singing and choosing flower from flower 42 with which was painted all her way.

52 As she turns, with the plants pressed 53 to the ground and within herself, woman who dances, 54 and foot before foot with difficulty puts,
55 she turned towards the reds and towards the yellows 56 little flowers towards me, not otherwise 57 than virgin who lowers the honest eyes;
58 and made my prayers be content, 59 so approaching herself, that the sweet sound 60 came to me with its intentions.

