106 in this height that is all dissolved 107 in the living air, such motion strikes, 108 and makes to sound the forest because it is dense;
109 and the struck plant so much is able, 110 that of its virtue the air impregnates 111 and that then, turning, around shakes;
112 and the other earth, according to as it is worthy 113 for itself and for its sky, conceives and begets 114 of diverse virtues diverse wood.

